arStrings.szText: "Who were you speaking with?"
My master, Ezra-Kan. He was once gatekeeper to the city of Necropolis, and now whispers from beyond the veil. The time has come for Rathma's faithful to return to the holy city.
Informative, earnest.

Speaking with my master, Ezra-Kan, from across the veil. He was once gatekeeper to the city of Necropolis. The time has come for Rathma's faithful, such as we, to return to the holy city.
Informative, earnest.

I’ve learned from locals that the lightless tunnels surrounding the city's stygian gates swarm with the spawn of hatred. They thrive in the shadows after Malthael's reapers butchered the necromancers.
Informative, then passionate about Malthael's butchery.

My master appointed a task to me. I, Kyros, shall open the city's gates once more and take his place as gatekeeper.
Informative, proud.
I’m unsure when the way to the gate will be cleared, but when it is, I ask that you join me there. I believe Rathma brought us together for a purpose.
Genuine ask for help.
